	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65032553"><p>&gt;"But they only need to work once to kill someone, and then you just throw it away."</p><p>No, not only do they need to work once, of which there is no guarantee, they also need to be effective (penetration/expansion/damage), and they also need to hit the target (accuracy/range).  This is why nobody serious about self-protection is going to carry around a single-round, unreliable, inaccurate, wimpy, piece of all-plastic junk.   Could it be useful?  Maybe.  I suppose it is better than nothing at all in some circ<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

